# Architecture

SolidJS core monorepo ‚Äî a declarative JavaScript UI library that compiles templates to real DOM nodes with fine-grained reactivity. Version 2.0 beta (pre-release, every release may be breaking).

## Monorepo Structure

PNPM workspaces + Turborepo. All packages version together (`2.0.0-beta.x`).

- **`solid-js`** (`packages/solid/`): Core runtime ‚Äî component model, flow controls, context, hydration. Wraps `@solidjs/signals` with a UI layer.
- **`@solidjs/web`** (`packages/solid-web/`): Web platform runtime ‚Äî `render`, `hydrate`, SSR methods, `Portal`, `Dynamic`. Delegates DOM ops to `dom-expressions`.
- **`@solidjs/h`** (`packages/solid-h/`): Hyperscript/JSX factory ‚Äî less-optimal JSX alternative.
- **`solid-element`** (`packages/solid-element/`): Web Components wrapper.
- **`solid-html`** (`packages/solid-html/`): Build-less tagged template literals.
- **`@solidjs/universal`** (`packages/solid-universal/`): Universal runtime for custom renderers.
- **`babel-preset-solid`** (`packages/babel-preset-solid/`): Babel preset for JSX compilation.
- **`test-integration`** (`packages/test-integration/`): Integration tests against external repos.

## Dependency Chain

```
@solidjs/signals  (reactive primitives)
       ‚Üì
   solid-js       (component model, flow controls, context, hydration)
       ‚Üì
  @solidjs/web    (DOM rendering, SSR, Portal, Dynamic)
       ‚Üì
  dom-expressions (external ‚Äî DOM operation runtime)
```

`solid-js` re-exports all reactivity primitives from `@solidjs/signals` and adds the component/JSX layer on top. `@solidjs/web` provides the platform-specific runtime.

## Component Model

Components are plain functions: `(props: P) => JSX.Element`. No classes, no hooks. Component creation is wrapped in `untrack()` to avoid reactive tracking during initialization.

Component types enforce children constraints:
- `Component<P>` ‚Äî no implicit children
- `VoidComponent<P>` ‚Äî forbids children
- `ParentComponent<P>` ‚Äî optional `JSX.Element` children
- `FlowComponent<P, C>` ‚Äî requires children of type `C`

## Reactivity Integration

All reactivity comes from `@solidjs/signals`:
- `createSignal()` ‚Üí `[getter, setter]`
- `createMemo()` ‚Üí derived computation
- `createEffect(compute, effect)` ‚Äî separate compute and effect phases
- `createStore()` ‚Üí proxy-based deep reactivity
- `flush()` ‚Äî updates are batched; must flush to process

## Flow Controls

Built on signals primitives: `For` (mapArray), `Repeat` (repeat), `Show` (createMemo), `Switch/Match` (children + memos), `Errored` (createErrorBoundary), `Boundary` (createBoundary), `Loading` (createLoadingBoundary).

All support `keyed` mode (identity comparison) vs non-keyed (truthiness). Function children in `Show`/`Match` receive narrowed accessors with stale-read protection.

## Build-time Constants

`_SOLID_DEV_` and `_DX_DEV_` are replaced at build time (see rollup configs). Use these for dev-only code to enable tree-shaking in production.

## Commands

- `pnpm install` ‚Äî install dependencies (pnpm 9.15+ required)
- `pnpm build` ‚Äî Turborepo build (all packages)
- `pnpm types` ‚Äî generate TypeScript declarations
- `pnpm test` ‚Äî run all tests + type tests
- `pnpm coverage` ‚Äî coverage reports
- `pnpm format` ‚Äî Prettier formatting (also runs on pre-commit)

## Key External Dependencies

- `@solidjs/signals` ‚Äî reactive primitives (separate repo)
- `dom-expressions` ‚Äî DOM operation runtime
- `seroval` / `seroval-plugins` ‚Äî serialization for SSR
- `babel-plugin-jsx-dom-expressions` ‚Äî JSX compilation
